                        <h3>Family terms for the parents</h3>
                        <p>
                            In East Frisian, one's own parents are often addressed with "mäem" and "bâb".
                            These terms correspond roughly to the English "mom" and "dad" - but they are used more frequently.
                            The equivalents for "mother" and "father" are "mauder" and "fóóer".
                        </p>
